{"lemma":"أَظْلَمِ","slug":"أَظْلَمِ","root":"ظ.ل.م","root_slug":"ظ-ل-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ظ-ل-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"أَظْلَم","root":"ظلم","pos":"N","occurrence_count":16},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n27639","n27641","n27662"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%B8%D9%92%D9%84%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to suffer injustice, to be wronged"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/iðˤ.ðˤa.la.ma/","/iðˤ.lim/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27639","headword_ar":"اظلم","root":"Zlm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", said of the night, (Fr, T, S, M, Msb, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zalima","text_ar":"ظَلِمَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Fr, T, S, K,) the latter with kesr, (S,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samiEa","text_ar":"سَمِعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) [erroneously written in the TT as from the M"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zalama","text_ar":"ظَلَمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It became dark;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it became black;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it came with its darkness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) It is said in the Kur [ii. 19],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA_i*aA A^aZolama Ealayohimo qaAmuwA","text_ar":"وَاـِذَا اَظْلَمَ عَلَيْهِمْ قَامُوا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And when it becomes dark to them they stand still"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; the verb being intrans.: or, accord. to the Ksh, and Bd follows it, it may be trans. [so that the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and when He makes"},{"kind":"text","text":"their place"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dark"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]; as is shown by another reading, which is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uZolimuwA","text_ar":"اُظْلِمُوا"},{"kind":"text","text":": accord. to AHei, it is known by transmission as only intrans.; but Z makes it to be trans. by itself; Ibn-Es-Saláh affirms it to be trans. and intrans.: and Az [so in the TA, but correctly ISd, in the M,] mentions the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"takal~ama faA^aZolama","text_ar":"تَكَلَّمَ فَاَظْلَمَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalayonaA AlbayEta","text_ar":"عَلَيْنَا البَيعتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He spoke, and made dark to us the house,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chamber,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tent"},{"kind":"text","text":"], meaning he made us to hear what we disliked, or hated, the verb being trans. (TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aZolamuwA","text_ar":"اَظْلَمُوا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They entered upon the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZalaAm","text_ar":"ظَلَام"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"darkness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beginning of night"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, M, Msb, K:) or, as in the Mufradát [of Er-Rághib],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they became in darkness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  And they said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^aZolamahu","text_ar":"مَا اَظْلَمَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA A^aDowaA^ahu","text_ar":"ما اَضْوَاَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How dark is it!"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How light,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bright, is it!"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; which is anomalous. (S, TA.)       -A2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AZlm","text_ar":"اظلم"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alv~agoru","text_ar":"الثَّغْرُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The front teeth glistened."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K.) Hence the saying [of a poet],"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A_i*aA maA A@jotalaY Alr~aAy^iY A_ilayohaA biTarofihi\n                      \n                     \n                        guruwba vanaAyaAhaA A^aDaA='a waA^aZolamaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as though meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When the beholder of her with his eye looks at the fineness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sharpness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guruwb","text_ar":"غُرُوب"},{"kind":"text","text":"is variously explained,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of her central teeth, it shines brightly, and glistens:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but Az plainly indicates another meaning; i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he sees"},{"kind":"text","text":"(lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lights on,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"finds,"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brightness and lustre;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for he immediately adds, without the intervention of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa","text_ar":"وَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awo","text_ar":"اَوْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", evidently in relation to this verse,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aDaA='a","text_ar":"اَضَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aYo A^aSaAba Dawo'FA waA^aZolama A^aSaAba ZalomFA","text_ar":"اَىْ اَصَابَ ضَوْءًا وَاَظْلَمَ اَصَابَ ظَلْمًا"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T:) [and ISd cites the verse above with the substitution of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biEaynihi","text_ar":"بِعَينِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biTarofihi","text_ar":"بِطَرْفِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaAra","text_ar":"اَنَارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aDaA='a","text_ar":"اَضَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"immediately after saying that]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aZolama","text_ar":"اَظْلَمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he looked at the teeth and saw lustre"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlZ~aloma","text_ar":"الظَّلْمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"). (M.) [In the K, next after the explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AZlm Alv~agoru","text_ar":"اظلم الثَّغْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"given above, it is added that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AZlm","text_ar":"اظلم"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a man signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSaAba ZalomFA","text_ar":"اَصَابَ ظَلْمًا"},{"kind":"text","text":": thus, with fet-h, to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Z","text_ar":"ظ"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to the TA: in my MS. copy of the K and in the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZulomFA","text_ar":"ظُلْمًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is doubtless a mistranscription.]"}],"source_refs":["Fr","T","S","M","Msb","K"]},{"entry_id":"n27641","headword_ar":"اِظَّلَمَ","root":"Zlm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiZoTalama","text_ar":"اِظْطَلَمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiT~alama","text_ar":"اِطَّلَمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M,) which last is [said to be] the most usual, (S,) [but I have mostly found the first to be used,] of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AifotaEala","text_ar":"اِفْتَعَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He took upon himself"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the bearing of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zulom","text_ar":"ظُلْم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wrong,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in spite of difficulty, trouble,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inconvenience:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he bore"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlZ~ulom","text_ar":"الظُّلْم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wrong,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,] (T, M, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"willingly, being able to resist;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AinoZalama","text_ar":"اِنْظَلَمَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies [thus likewise, or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he bore"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlZ~ulom","text_ar":"الظُّلْم"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, M, K.)"}],"source_refs":["T","S","M","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n27662","headword_ar":"اَظْلَمُ","root":"Zlm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"More,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most, wrongful, unjust, injurious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tyrannical, in conduct"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. El-Muärrij says, I heard an Arab of the desert say to his companion,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aZolamiY waA^aZolamuka fafaEala A@ll~`hu bihi","text_ar":"اَظْلَمِى وَاَظْلَمُكَ فَفَعَلَ ا@للّٰهُ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The more wrongful in conduct of me and of thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may God do to him"},{"kind":"text","text":"what He will do; i. e. may God punish him]. (T.) [And] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laEana","text_ar":"لَعَنَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@ll~`hu A^aZolamiY waA^aZolamaka","text_ar":"ا@للّٰهُ اَظْلَمِى وَاَظْلَمَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God curse"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the more wrongful in conduct of us."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K. [But in the TA, a doubt is intimated as to the correctness of this latter saying.]) One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahuwa A^aZolamu","text_ar":"لَهُوَ اَظْلَمُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino Hay~apK","text_ar":"مِنْ حَيَّةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is more wrongful in conduct than a serpent"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: because it comes to a burrow which it has not excavated, and makes its abode in it: (Fr, T:) for it comes to the burrow of the [lizard called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dab~","text_ar":"ضَبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and eats its young one, and takes up its abode in its burrow. (TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hay~apN","text_ar":"حَيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aZolamu","text_ar":"الاَظْلَمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an appellation of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dab~","text_ar":"ضَبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; because it eats its young ones. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Fr","T"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%A3%D8%B8%D9%84%D9%85/","headword_ar":"أظلم","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_52","lexicon_en":"Yāqūt al-Ḥamawī, Muʿjam al-Buldān (d. 1229)","lexicon_ar":"معجم البلدان لياقوت الحموي","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=78074#227fff","body_html":"<span class=\"title1\">أظلم:</span><span> جبل في أرض بني سليم، وأظلم أيضا:</span><br><span>جبل في أرض الحبشة به معدن صفر، وأظلم:</span><br><span>بالشّعيبة من بطن الرّمّة، وقال الأصمعي عند ذكره جبال مكة: أظلم الجبل الأسود من ذات حبيس، قال الحصين بن حمام المرّي:</span><br><span>فليت أبا بشر رأى كرّ خيلنا </span><span class=\"red\">...</span><span> وخيلهم، بين السّتار وأظلما</span><br><span>نطاردهم، نستنقذ الجرد بالقنا، </span><span class=\"red\">...</span><span> ويستنقذون السّمهريّ المقوّما</span><br><span>عشيّة لا تغني الرماح مكانها، </span><span class=\"red\">...</span><span> ولا النّبل إلا المشرفيّ المصمّما</span>"}]}}